Telefonica, Turk Telekom Form Alliance, Telecompaper.com Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-04-15T09:05:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/telefonica-turk-telekom-form-alliance-telecompaper-com-says.html
Telefonica SA (TEF) ’s German unit and
 Turk Telekomunikasyon AS (TTKOM)  announced a strategic alliance to
market communications services that use both operators’ fixed,
mobile services and brands,  Telecompaper.com website  reported
today.  “Under the partnership, a wide range of services will be
available to customers from the summer, regardless of whether
they are in Germany or Turkey,” said Rene Schuster, chief
executive of Telefonica’s German unit, according to the website.  Avea Iletisim Hizmetleri AS, a Turkish mobile operator
owned by Turk Telekom, and Telefonica will offer “tailored
services for Turks and Germany and in their home country,”
Schuster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 